      "Aligned with the Saudi Green Initiative, eco-friendly [event management](/services/corporate-events) is reshaping how [conferences](/services/conferences) and corporate gatherings are planned across the Kingdom. This guide covers the practical measures that make a meaningful difference.",
      "## Sustainable Venue Selection",
      "Venues with demonstrable sustainability credentials — LEED certification, ISO 14001 environmental management, documented energy efficiency and waste management programs — are increasingly requested by international corporations hosting events in Saudi Arabia. When evaluating venues, ask specifically about energy sourcing and metering, water conservation systems, waste segregation and recycling infrastructure, and the venue's policy on single-use plastics.",
      "## Waste Reduction in Practice",
      "A practical waste reduction policy for corporate events covers: digital invitations and registration (eliminating paper-based materials), reusable or compostable catering supplies, comprehensive on-site recycling with clearly labeled stations, and working with caterers who can donate surplus food to local organizations. Implement a zero-single-use-plastic policy and communicate it to all vendors as a contract requirement. Relying on traditional printed collateral when digital alternatives are available adds cost and waste without adding value.",
