      "When booking live entertainment, secure all necessary [GEA permits](/blog/gea-event-permit-guide-saudi-arabia) well in advance — Jeddah Season creates high demand for GEA-licensed performers and permits take 4–8 weeks to process.",
      "## 2. Live Performances at the Right Scale",
      "High-caliber live performances — whether regional musicians, international acts, or strong theatrical productions — set the tone for what kind of event yours is. The choice of performer communicates brand values, and matching that correctly matters as much as production quality. Allocate entertainment as a proportion of total event budget rather than minimizing it; production quality for live performance (sound, lighting, stage) typically equals or exceeds the performer fee at well-run corporate events.",
      "## 3. Culinary Experiences That Go Beyond Catering",
      "During Jeddah Season, the city's culinary offering is at its highest level. Corporate events that use only a standard buffet miss an opportunity. Consider: interactive cooking stations with skilled chefs, tasting menus that work through Hejazi cuisine with proper context, or collaboration with a recognized Jeddah restaurant for an off-site dinner component.",
